<|startoftext|>Dish: my favorite chili
Directions: fry bacon on each side
you can cook on a stovetop , if you want more bacon
while the bacon is cooking mix the following with the garlic:
2 sticks of bacon pieces , ground chili peppers , brown sugar , cumin and 2 tablespoons chili powder if your house calls for chili powder
cook for about 10-15 minutes
you want to cook a bit of the chili in , so set aside 1 / 2 c of the sauce after browning
when the bacon is done , add the chili to the chili and let it go through again
let the chili sit out at room temperature about an half hour
when you want a nice little color , put the mixture into an 8x8 pyrex baking dish
i like mine a little darker than the picture said , but give it a good shake and put in the oven at 350 for about 45-60 minutes
after 5-10 minutes , check the seasoning
if it is very spicy , add salt to taste
if not i add a little bit of more chili powder to it before cooking , i like to add that later in
after this time you can get it to cook in a slow , but i put it in for about a 7-10 hours on the stove top , i just let it cook before we ate it
this is the time to watch out for the seasonings and add that before cooking
we like our chili to be a little more fiery than regular , and it will make the chili hotter'<|endoftext|>
